PLOGHELP INTEGER                              Chris Mellish, August 1982
                                Revised by Kathryn Seifert  October 1986

Predicate which tests whether its argument is an integer

    ?- integer(X).

Keywords: integer, numbers, arithmetic


A goal of the form:
    ?- integer(X).
succeeds if X is an integer.


